        <name>16.1.2.3 Geometric sequence a and r</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find \(a,\ r\) for the geometric sequence \(\displaystyle{{@a1@},\ {@a2@},\ {@a3@},\dots}\)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(a = \) [[input:ans_a]] [[validation:ans_a]] [[feedback:prt_a]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(r = \) [[input:ans_r]] [[validation:ans_r]] [[feedback:prt_r]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We are given the geometric sequence \(\displaystyle{{@a1@},\ {@a2@},\ {@a3@},\dots}\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a geometric sequence:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The value of \(a\) is always given by the first term of the sequence. Hence, \(a = {@aa@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The value of \(r\) is given by the ratio between any two consecutive terms in the sequence. Hence, \(r = \displaystyle{@rr@}\).&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
